=== band-45 (shallow flat) edge geometry vs ARPES ===
band-45 (spin-pol cell): top edge -0.341 eV, center -0.425 eV, bottom -0.508 eV (W=0.167)
band-44: top -0.478, center -0.567, bottom -0.655
Measured ARPES (arXiv:2102.08979): flat d-band CENTER ~ -0.10 eV below E_F
Measured ARPES (Kang 2001.11738): d_xz/d_yz flat band ~ -0.20 eV; QGT band (2412.17809) ~ measured
=> Our PBE shallow flat-band TOP edge (-0.34 eV) is ~0.24 eV deeper than the ARPES center (-0.10 eV).
   PBE over-deepens the SAME shallow band by ~0.2-0.3 eV (known PBE flat-band offset, H_024: ~140meV ARPES offset).

=> doping to ARPES depth -0.10 eV = 0.20 h/f.u. (PHYSICAL); to PBE band-center -0.44 = 1.58 h/f.u. (EXTREME)
   The 8x gap between them IS the flat-band DOS pileup: most of the band's weight is in the -0.34..-0.51 eV slab.
